                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 3 pg. 100",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 3 pg. 100",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq024xj"
                    },
                    "page": 100
                }
            ],
            "subtype": "sidebar",
            "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
            "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
            "image": {
                "type": "image",
                "name": "Additional Lore",
                "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
            },
            "html": "Flumphs find great satisfaction in making and fulfilling oaths. They feel rewarded when keeping even a small promise, and pepper their social interactions with little agreements and accords. They take deception personally, and don't understand the concept of white lies. After fulfilling an oath, a flumph is sure to inform the other party. Incomplete oaths make flumphs anxious, causing them to check in if they believe they've been promised something\u2014often with irritating frequency."
        }
    ],
